  <summary>10/18/2005--Introduced.
Permits statues honoring deceased citizens of U.S. territories (American Samoa, Guam, the Commonwealth of Puerto Rico, and the U.S. Virgin Islands) to be placed in Statuary Hall. Limits such statues to one per jurisdiction.</summary>
